<h3>Panel groups (.Panels)</h3>
<p>If you wrap you panels with a parent element with the class <code>Panels</code>, the margin is removed from the individual panel components, creating a connected look.</p>

<div class="docs-example">
  <div class="Panels">
    <div class="Panel Panel--box">
      <p>Top panel</p>
    </div>
    <div class="Panel Panel--box">
      <p>Middle panel</p>
    </div>
    <div class="Panel Panel--box">
      <p>Bottom panel</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="docs-code docs-code--html">
  <pre><code class="html">&lt;div class=&quot;Panels&quot;&gt;
  &lt;div class=&quot;Panel Panel--box&quot;&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;Top panel&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;div class=&quot;Panel Panel--box&quot;&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;Middle panel&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;div class=&quot;Panel Panel--box&quot;&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;Bottom panel&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
</div>

